## Key Features

- Fine-tuned Arabic Large Language Model (LLM)
- Structured pipeline for generating Arabic instructions for APIs
- Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) approach for reducing hallucinations
- Evaluation metrics include AST sub-tree matching and cosine similarity

## How To Use

To clone and run this application, you'll need [Git](https://git-scm.com) and [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en/download/) (which comes with [npm](http://npmjs.com)) installed on your computer. From your command line:

```bash
# Clone this repository
$ git clone https://github.com/yourusername/AraGorilla

# Go into the repository
$ cd AraGorilla

# Install dependencies
$ npm install

# Run the app
$ npm start
